Backgrounds are fundamental to establishing emphasis and hierarchy. We already use a flexible, accessible background system across all touchpoints, and these tokens replicate that system while also providing dark-mode equivalents. As a general rule, background tokens should be applied to screen backgrounds, but they can also be used for components when needed. If you have any questions about how to apply the background tokens, please contact the GEL team.

{% tokens
   tokens=[{tokenName: "background-white", description: "If you need a white background use this token.", fillColour: "background-white", strokeColour: "border-muted-soft", circleType: "solid", restricted: false, new: false}, {tokenName: "background-pale", description: "If you need a grey background use this token. Note: this token replaces the current Background colour style.", fillColour: "background-pale", strokeColour: "border-muted-soft", circleType: "solid", restricted: false, new: false}, {tokenName: "background-faint", description: "If you need a light grey background use this token. Note: this token replaces the current Light colour style. Do not use this token as a screen background.", fillColour: "background-faint", strokeColour: "border-muted-soft", circleType: "solid", restricted: false, new: false}] /%}
